<paragraph id="E1B2A5963FB988858015AEB09EC519CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56D29DDEBC61C4BFC0E4BBA93CBDA673" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
Guyana. Region: Potaro-Siparuni. Mt. Ayanganna, east face, plateau above second of four escarpments. 1380 m, 
<geoCoordinate id="BC44C252D5B7BDF072EF7F1AF4391721" degrees="05" direction="north" minutes="22.550" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="5.3758335">05°22.550'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="E13A00D99A02B569E2B2441B1D3B1B56" degrees="059" direction="west" minutes="58.350" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="-59.9725">059°58.350'W</geoCoordinate>
. Scrub forest on sandstone and peat, with 
<taxonomicName id="22FBCDA3159EDDD412AD7BD34CACADF2" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clusia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A680B7F16E18A6277FEEDA32EFBCC19E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Clusia</emphasis>
